Package: lwdidR
Title: Lee-Wooldridge Difference-in-Differences via Unit-Specific Transformations
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: person("Xiang", "Ao", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "xiangao@example.com")
Author: Xiang Ao [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Xiang Ao <xiangao@example.com>
Description: Implements the Lee & Wooldridge (2025) panel difference-in-differences
    estimator via unit-specific pre-treatment transformations (demean, detrend,
    demeanq, detrendq). Supports both common-timing and staggered adoption designs
    with cohort-specific aggregation. Inference options include homoskedastic OLS,
    HC1, HC3 (manual sandwich), cluster-robust, wild cluster bootstrap
    (Rademacher weights), and permutation/randomisation inference. The last two are
    distribution-free and recommended at small N or with non-normal errors.
    Replicates results from Lee & Wooldridge (2025) Section 7.2 (Castle Doctrine
    law application).
